<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Day 3: The VIP Manifest</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to engagement</a>
    <div class="brand brand-sm">
      <span class="brand-mark">⛨</span>
      <span>CySER Workshop · Skyway engagement</span>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>Day 3 · The VIP Manifest</h1>
      <p class="desc">Skyway's customer-service tool lets staff look up any booking by ID. The "any" is doing a lot of work in that sentence.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story-box">
      <strong>The story.</strong> The staff portal is supposed to be internal. The lookup endpoint takes a booking
      ID and returns the booking. With <strong>zero authorization check</strong>. Anyone who reaches the page can
      enumerate every customer's record. Ops also let slip in their notes that one of today's bookings is
      flagged "VIP" with a special comp code. Find that record.
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="fake-website">
        <div class="fake-navbar">
          <span>🛩️ Skyway · Public Site</span>
          <span>Home · About · Press</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fake-body">
          <h2>Skyway Airlines.</h2>
          <p>Everything we publish is on this homepage. Staff tooling is internal-only.</p>
          <p style="opacity:0.6">(Search engines have been politely asked not to index our private paths.)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tools-section">
        <h3>🛠 How to attack this</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Start at <a href="/robots.txt" target="_blank"><code>/robots.txt</code></a>. It leaks which paths Skyway is hiding from search engines</li>
          <li>Visit the hidden <code>/staff/</code> landing page (the staff portal)</li>
          <li>Use the booking lookup. IDs run <code>1001,1100</code> per their note</li>
          <li>The VIP record is one of them. Enumerate to find it (curl loop or sweep manually)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Enumerate fast with a one-liner</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>Browser Console:</strong><br>
          <code style="white-space:pre">for (let i=1001;i&lt;=1100;i++) {
  const r = await fetch('/staff/booking?id='+i);
  const t = await r.text();
  if (t.includes('flag{')) { console.log(i, t.match(/flag\{[^}]+\}/)[0]); break; }
}</code></p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch3')">Submit finding</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
